': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='or an individual appraisal of existing housing that was not previously occupied.\n\nThe certification provides that the builder or other party will not decline to sell the appraised property to a prospective purchaser because of his or her\n\nNote : This requirement is satisfied by completion of VA Form 26-8791, VA Affirmative Marketing Certification.\n\nVeteran Equal Housing Certification', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Veteran Equal Housing Certification\n\nParticipant is an Entity,\n\n-\n\n,\n\n-\n\nParticipants who Violate Statutory Provisions and Regulations,\n\n-\n\nProbationary Period,\n\n-\n\nProgram Participants,\n\n-\n\nReasons For Lender Check,\n\n-\n\nResponsbilities of Lender,\n\n-\n\nSanctions,\n\n-\n\nScope of Exclusion,\n\n-\n\nSubmitting Loans,\n\n-\n\nSubstantive or Repetitive Errors -\n\nAppeal Rights to all Program Participants,\n\nAppeal Rights to all Program Participants,\n\n-', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Appeal Rights to all Program Participants,\n\nAppeal Rights to all Program Participants,\n\n-\n\nCause and Treatment Codes,\n\n-\n\nCauses for LDP,\n\n-\n\nDebarment,\n\n-\n\nDebarment or Suspension Causes,\n\n-\n\nDebarred Loan Guaranty Participants,\n\n-\n\nDetermining Reasonable Value and Issuing CRVs,\n\n-\n\nDisregard for VA Requirements - Example,\n\n-\n\nEqual Housing Certification,\n\n-\n\nExcluded Party,\n\n-\n\nFailure to Meet Qualification Requirements - Example,\n\n-', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='-\n\nEqual Housing Certification,\n\n-\n\nExcluded Party,\n\n-\n\nFailure to Meet Qualification Requirements - Example,\n\n-\n\nFalse Lender Certification,\n\n-\n\nFull Exclusion,\n\n-\n\nGovernment at Risk,\n\n-\n\nGSA List,\n\n-\n\nIdentifying Excluded Parties Internet Address,\n\n-\n\nJurisdiction Restrictions,\n\n-\n\nLAPP Privilege,\n\n-\n\nLDP as Reciprocal Action,\n\n-\n\nLDP Exceptions,\n\n-\n\nLDP Party Information,\n\n-\n\nLDP Time Period,\n\n-\n\nLimited Denial of Participation (LDP),\n\n-', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='-\n\nLDP Exceptions,\n\n-\n\nLDP Party Information,\n\n-\n\nLDP Time Period,\n\n-\n\nLimited Denial of Participation (LDP),\n\n-\n\nCause and Treatment Codes,\n\n-\n\nCauses for LDP,\n\n-\n\nDebarment,\n\n-\n\nDebarment or Suspension Causes,\n\n-\n\nDebarred Loan Guaranty Participants,\n\n-\n\nDetermining Reasonable Value and Issuing CRVs,\n\n-\n\nDisregard for VA Requirements - Example,\n\n-\n\nEqual Housing Certification,\n\n-\n\nExcluded Party,\n\n-\n\nFailure to Meet Qualification Requirements', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='-\n\nEqual Housing Certification,\n\n-\n\nExcluded Party,\n\n-\n\nFailure to Meet Qualification Requirements\n\nUnfair Marketing Practices,\n\n-\n\nUnresolved Deficiencies,\n\n-\n\nVA Business With Other Participants,\n\n-\n\nVA Loan Guaranty Program,\n\n-\n\nVA May Impose Sanctions,\n\n-\n\nVA Regulations on Debarments or\n\nWithdrawal for an Indefinite Period,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal For Proper Cause,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\n-\n\nYears,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\nDays,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\nDays,', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\n-\n\nYears,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\nDays,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Period:\n\nDays,\n\n-\n\nWithdrawal Time Periods,\n\n-\n\nMonetary Penalty,\n\n-\n\nNature of Exclusion,\n\n-\n\nNon Procurement List,\n\n-\n\nNotice of Sanction,\n\n-\n\nOther Program Participants,\n\n-\n\nPartial Exclusion,\n\n-\n\nParticipant Also A Veteran,\n\n-\n\nChapter 18. Servicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP)\n\nOverview\n\nIn this chapter\n\nThis chapter contains the following topics.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Overview\n\nIn this chapter\n\nThis chapter contains the following topics.\n\nTopic Topic Description See Page 1 Purpose and Eligibility Requirements 18-2 2 Applying for Authority 18-4 3 Training and Initial Test Case Reviews 18-5 4 Servicer Responsibilities 18-7 5 Processing Procedures 18-8 6 Servicer Quality Control System Requirements 18-10\n\nPurpose and Eligibility Requirements', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Servicers of Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) guaranteed loans may be granted authority, under Servicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP), to review liquidation appraisals, and issue the Notice of Value (NOV) without VA involvement. The servicer exercises its SAPP authority through an employee who is VA-approved as a SAPP Staff Appraisal Reviewer (SAR). Once a SAR has satisfied the SAPP training and initial case review requirements (see section 3 of this', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Reviewer (SAR). Once a SAR has satisfied the SAPP training and initial case review requirements (see section 3 of this chapter), their SAPP authority may be used for eligible properties (those secured by VA-guaranteed loans) in any location within the United States and its territories. The purpose of SAPP is to reduce the time required for servicers of VA loans to receive the NOV.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='requirements (see section 3 of this chapter), their SAPP authority may be used for eligible properties (those secured by VA-guaranteed loans) in any location within the United States and its territories. The purpose of SAPP is to reduce the time required for servicers of VA loans to receive the NOV.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Important : It is the SAR’s responsibility to stay informed about any local VA processing requirements unique to the VA jurisdiction in which a property is located.\n\nTo be granted SAPP authority, the servicer must have:\n\nb. Servicer Eligibility Requirements', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='To be granted SAPP authority, the servicer must have:\n\nb. Servicer Eligibility Requirements\n\na VA servicer identification number (ID), an association with a single lender having a VA lender ID, and an effective quality control (QC) system that ensures the adequacy and quality of its SARs. (See section\n\nof this chapter.)\n\nNote: Under SAPP, a servicer may only have an association with a single lender.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='of this chapter.)\n\nNote: Under SAPP, a servicer may only have an association with a single lender.\n\nThe servicer exercises its SAPP authority through an employee who is a VA- approved SAR. A SAR must:\n\nc. SAR Eligibility Requirements\n\nContinued on next page\n\nPurpose and Eligibility Requirements, Continued\n\nThe SAR’s work experience must indicate that he or she has:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='general knowledge of the principles, methods, practices, and techniques appraising and the ability to apply that knowledge, the ability to review the work of others and recognize deviations from accepted appraisal principles and practices, the ability to detect errors in computations, and the ability to detect conclusions that are not supported.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='It is also desirable for the SAR to have knowledge of general realty practices and principles related to real property valuation, skill in collecting and assembling data, and the ability to prepare clear and concise reports.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Note : Three years experience related to the Housing and Urban Development (HUD) Direct Endorsement (DE) program satisfies the experience requirement, provided all other application requirements are satisfied.\n\nd. SAR Conflicts of Interest', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='d. SAR Conflicts of Interest\n\nThere must be no conflict of interest between the SAR’s role and any other activities that he or she conducts. Examples of other activities that would constitute a conflict of interest include, but are not limited to:\n\nthe SAR being on the VA fee appraisal panel, or the SAR being employed by or performing appraisal review services for another lender/servicer.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Applying for Authority\n\na. Application and Fees\n\nThe nominating senior officer of the servicer and the nominee must jointly complete the Staff Appraisal Reviewer (SAR) application.\n\nSAR applicants must attach a resume showing they possess the three years requisite experience outlined in section 1 of this chapter.\n\nA $100 processing fee must accompany the application package.\n\nb. Notification of VA Decision', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='A $100 processing fee must accompany the application package.\n\nb. Notification of VA Decision\n\nDepartment of Veterans Affairs (VA) Central Office will review the application and send a letter of preliminary approval or rejection. In some cases, VA will need to request additional information from both the nominee and the senior officer in order to make a determination.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Receipt of a letter of preliminary approval will authorize the nominee to schedule Servicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP) SAR training.\n\nc. SAR ID Number\n\nWhen a SAR already has a Lender Appraisal Processing Program (LAPP) SAR ID number, the number will also be used as the SAPP SAR ID.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='If a SAR begins work for a new servicer, the SAR’s SAPP authority automatically ceases and does not transfer to the new servicer. To reinstate the SAR’s SAPP authority, the new servicer employer must promptly submit to VA:\n\nd. SAR Employed By New Servicer\n\nThe servicer may request a waiver for the training and case review requirements for that SAR by including:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='the SAR’s VA-issued ID number on the application, and a statement that the SAR has processed SAPP cases within the last year.\n\nTraining and Initial Test Case Reviews', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Training and Initial Test Case Reviews\n\nStaff Appraisal Reviewers (SARs) with preliminary approval may not independently review liquidation appraisal reports and issue liquidation Notice of Values (NOVs), without the involvement of Department of Veterans Affairs (VA), until they receive final approval. To obtain final approval, the SAR must complete the following:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='VA Central Office staff will provide SAPP SAR training at the request of the servicer and VA Regional Loan Center (RLC) staff will conduct the initial test case reviews.\n\nb. Test Case Procedures', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Upon completion of SAR training, SARs may begin submitting their test cases in The Appraisal System (TAS) for VA review. Only one test case should be pending at any time; SARs should not submit an additional test case until the results of a previously submitted test case are known. RLC staff will notify the SAR about the results of the review. The RLC staff performing the review of test cases must complete the liquidation appraisal review and issue the NOV within five workdays', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='the review of test cases must complete the liquidation appraisal review and issue the NOV within five workdays from the date the case is submitted by the SAR.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='The following table outlines the steps for processing SAPP SAR test cases. Please note that these are the same steps for processing any SAPP cases, except for the requirement of VA involvement.\n\nSAR accesses the VA E-Appraisal application in the Veterans Information Portal (VIP or Portal) and retrieves a SAPP appraisal. (Only SAPP appraisals associated with the SAR’s company may be retrieved.)', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='SAR reviews the appraisal report for completeness and conformity with industry-accepted appraisal practices and techniques, and for compliance with applicable VA directives and general and liquidation appraisal requirements in chapter\n\nThe SAR must resolve any concerns with the appraiser. (Report any contact with the appraiser and the results in “Processing Notes” when issuing the NOV.)', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Continued on next page\n\nTraining and Initial Test Case Reviews, Continued\n\nb. Test Case Procedures (continued)\n\nStep Description\n\nSAR determines the as-is value of the property, which must be supported by the reviewed appraisal report. (Make entries in “Processing Notes” to clarify or justify actions that are not self- explanatory.)', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='SAR accesses TAS in VIP, selects “Issue Liquidation NOV,” and inputs the required data to generate an NOV. (TAS will not allow SARs with preliminary approval to issue NOVs; they may only be saved as NOV test cases awaiting review by the RLC. (Upon receipt of SAR final approval, TAS will allow issuance of the NOV without VA involvement.) Note: The SAR must notify the RLC of jurisdiction when a test case has been submitted in TAS.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='VA RLC staff will review the following for all test cases and a percentage of subsequent cases: appraisal report, any related documents, the saved test case NOV, and processing notes, for any contacts with the appraiser, processing delays and clarification and/or justification of processing actions.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='VA staff will issue the NOV. The SAR will be notified of the result(s) of the VA test case review and the SAR’s performance file will be documented.\n\nprocessing notes, for any contacts with the appraiser, processing delays and clarification and/or justification of processing actions.\n\nc. Continuing Education by VA', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='c. Continuing Education by VA\n\nAs needed, VA will notify SAPP SARs of supplemental training opportunities or additional training requirements.\n\nServicer Responsibilities\n\nServicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP) authority is a privilege delegated to servicers at VA’s discretion. Servicers maintain this privilege by complying with all applicable SAPP-related requirements, including:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Furthermore, servicers are expected to exercise due diligence in processing SAPP cases. VA considers due diligence to be care that is properly expected from, and ordinarily exercised by, a reasonable and prudent servicer that is entirely dependent on the subject property as a security to protect its investment.\n\nIf VA finds proper cause, the privilege extended to servicers under SAPP may be:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='If VA finds proper cause, the privilege extended to servicers under SAPP may be:\n\nReference: For more information, refer to chapter 17.\n\nb. Servicer and SAR Changes\n\nThe servicer must notify VA Central Office if:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='The servicer must notify VA Central Office if:\n\nthere is a change in ownership, merger, or acquisition, or a SAR is no longer employed or is no longer functioning as a SAR for the servicer. (In such cases, the SAR’s SAPP authority automatically ceases and the servicer’s eligibility to participate in SAPP is terminated if that individual was the servicer’s onl y SAR on staff.)\n\nProcessing Procedures', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Processing Procedures\n\na. Property Eligibility\n\nThe subject property must be secured by a Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) guaranteed loan that is proceeding toward liquidation.\n\nServicers may authorize parties to order appraisals on their behalf (i.e., law firms). Those parties must register in the Veterans Information Portal (VIP) under their own name as an “Other Requestor.”', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='If the agent… Then… is acting on behalf of an approved Servicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP) servicer and is authorized by that servicer, he or she may request VA SAPP appraisals. requests an appraisal, he or she must use his or her own log-in identification (ID) to request appraisals. An appraisal cannot be requested unless the sponsoring servicer is known at the time of the request. Note: In requesting an appraisal, the authorized agent is making the required', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='is known at the time of the request. Note: In requesting an appraisal, the authorized agent is making the required certifications on behalf of the sponsoring servicer. receives notification the completed liquidation appraisal report has been uploaded in E-Appraisal, he or she must notify the sponsoring servicer or their Staff Appraisal Reviewer (SAR) that the appraisal was uploaded in E-Appraisal.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Note: In requesting an appraisal, the authorized agent is making the required certifications on behalf of the sponsoring servicer. he or she must notify the sponsoring servicer or their Staff Appraisal Reviewer (SAR) that the appraisal was uploaded in E\n\nAppraisal.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Note: When making the request, be sure to provide accurate information on the location of the keys to a vacant property in item 24 of VA Form 26-1805, VA Request for Determination of Reasonable Value, as well as the telephone number of the party requesting the liquidation appraisal in item 40. This may require additional instructions from servicers when referring cases to foreclosing attorneys, if the attorneys are the parties ordering the liquidation appraisals.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Processing Procedures, Continued', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='If the appraiser still cannot gain access, he or she must document the actions taken to obtain access to the subject vacant property in an e-mail to the Construction & Valuation (C&V) section of jurisdiction. C&V will then forward the appraiser’s email to the Regional Loan Center’s Loan Administration Officer, who will forward it to the appropriate servicer personnel.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Time delays caused by an appraiser’s inability to access a property can result in postponed liquidation sales. Because such delays are beyond the control of the appraiser, C&V “stops the clock” on the appraiser’s timeliness requirements until access is obtained. However, in most cases, VA does not view delays as beyond the control of the servicer, and therefore the servicer may suffer curtailment of interest on the loan if a sale cannot be completed timely due to delays in', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='the servicer may suffer curtailment of interest on the loan if a sale cannot be completed timely due to delays in the appraiser obtaining access to a property.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='d. Liquidation Appraisal Requirements\n\nIf a SAR is reluctant to issue the Notice of Value (NOV) due to the difficulty or complexity of the case, the SAR may request that the VA Regional Loan Center (RLC) of jurisdiction issue the NOV.\n\nServicer Quality Control System Requirements\n\na. Introduction', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Servicer Quality Control System Requirements\n\na. Introduction\n\nTo qualify for Servicer Appraisal Processing Program (SAPP) authority, the servicer must have an effective quality control (QC) system that ensures the adequacy and quality of its staff appraisal reviews. This QC system must be independent of the servicer’s loan servicing operation.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Upon request, the servicer must agree to furnish Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) with findings and information about the system. The senior officer must certify on each Staff Appraisal Reviewer (SAR) application that the QC system meets the requirements detailed in this section.\n\nb. QC Reviewers', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='b. QC Reviewers\n\nReviews of the SAR’s work may be performed by an independent party or independent internal audit division that reports directly to the servicer’s chief executive officer. QC personnel should possess:\n\nc. Frequency and Scope of Reviews\n\nPerform desk reviews of each SAR’s appraisal reviews on a monthly basis. The sample size should be no less than:', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='five percent of the SAR’s SAPP cases processed monthly, or a minimum number of cases per month (for example, five cases).\n\nThere must be a procedure for expanding the scope of the reviews if a pattern of deficiencies is identified.\n\nd. QC Review Criteria\n\nthe overall quality of the SAR’s appraisal review, and the appropriateness of the reasonable value determination.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Servicer Quality Control System Requirements, Continued\n\nThe QC system must provide for written notification of deficiencies cited as a result of audits on quarterly reviews to:\n\nThe QC system must require senior management to:\n\npromptly initiate and document actions to correct deficiencies, and provide SARs with corrective instructions.\n\ng. Review of VA Fee Panel Appraisals', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='g. Review of VA Fee Panel Appraisals\n\nIn addition to reviews of the SAR’s work, random field reviews of VA fee panel appraisals should be performed. These reviews can be done by:\n\nan independent appraiser on a contract basis.\n\nNote : Any substantive negative findings should be formally reported to the VA Regional Loan Center (RLC) where the appraiser is a member of the fee panel.', lookup_str='', metadata={'source': 'Lender_Handbook_VA_Pamphlet_Complete.pdf'}, lookup_index=0), Document(page_content='Appendix A: Listing of VA Offices\n\nOverview\n\nIn this chapter\n\nThis appendix contains the following topics.\n\nTopic Topic Name See Page 1 How to Use This Appendix A-2 2 Table of VA Offices A-3\n\n1. How to Use This Appendix\n\nChange Date\n\n• This section has been changed to revise the re